They should not be construed as
a guarantee of future releases.

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:44.355
I think I've done my diligence.

00:14:44.355 --> 00:14:45.730
But we know that
simply releasing

00:14:45.730 --> 00:14:47.355
a new version of the
library every year

00:14:47.355 --> 00:14:48.730
isn't the whole story.

00:14:48.730 --> 00:14:51.760
Current versions of the API
have an unpredictable support

00:14:51.760 --> 00:14:54.280
window, which means you don't
know when you need to update

00:14:54.280 --> 00:14:56.680
to the latest version.

00:14:56.680 --> 00:14:58.900
We think predictability
is really important,

00:14:58.900 --> 00:15:00.460
and that's why
starting today, we're

00:15:00.460 --> 00:15:02.920
announcing the deprecation
of previous integrations

00:15:02.920 --> 00:15:06.870
with Play Billing, AIDL,
and Billing Library 1.x.

00:15:06.870 --> 00:15:10.090
But further, we're announcing
this predictable and consistent

00:15:10.090 --> 00:15:12.340
deprecation and
sunsetting schedule.

00:15:12.340 --> 00:15:15.700
Each year, the API version
will advance by 1--

00:15:15.700 --> 00:15:18.430
as we mentioned, a new
major release of each I/O.

00:15:18.430 --> 00:15:21.340
Within one year following
each major release, new apps

00:15:21.340 --> 00:15:23.140
and app updates
will need to target

00:15:23.140 --> 00:15:25.675
the latest version of the
Billing Library or higher.

00:15:25.675 --> 00:15:27.550
So each release will
continue to be supported

00:15:27.550 --> 00:15:29.830
for an additional year to
give you time to integrate

00:15:29.830 --> 00:15:31.510
to the newest version.

00:15:31.510 --> 00:15:33.400
And again, going
forward, this process

00:15:33.400 --> 00:15:35.110
is meant to be very lightweight.

00:15:35.110 --> 00:15:37.870
Simply change the build target
to point to the latest version,

00:15:37.870 --> 00:15:40.300
and you're good to go.

00:15:40.300 --> 00:15:42.150
So here, you can see
the two-year lifecycle

00:15:42.150 --> 00:15:45.070
of each major version
of the Billing Library.

00:15:45.070 --> 00:15:47.337
And because we are announcing
a new release cadence,

00:15:47.337 --> 00:15:49.170
we want to make sure
you have plenty of time

00:15:49.170 --> 00:15:51.360
to migrate your
existing integration.

00:15:51.360 --> 00:15:54.685
Whether you're currently using
AIDL or Billing Library 1.x,

00:15:54.685 --> 00:15:56.310
we're giving the full
two years for you

00:15:56.310 --> 00:15:59.140
to migrate your integration.

00:15:59.140 --> 00:16:01.780
Next year, you can see the
plan to release Billing Library

00:16:01.780 --> 00:16:05.597
3.0, which will be supported
as well for two years.

00:16:05.597 --> 00:16:07.930
And two years from now, you
can see that Billing Library

00:16:07.930 --> 00:16:10.300
2.0 will reach its end of life.

00:16:10.300 --> 00:16:13.120
And all new apps and app updates
should be using Billing Library

00:16:13.120 --> 00:16:14.800
3.0 by that time.

00:16:14.800 --> 00:16:17.980
This release and support cadence
will continue each year going

00:16:17.980 --> 00:16:20.800
forward, with each I/O featuring
a new major release being

00:16:20.800 --> 00:16:27.580
available and releases from
